sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM survival_statistics 
WHERE voyage_id = 1 AND survived_count IS NOT NULL;

external_knowledge:
'southern port' refers to 'Southampton'; survival status is categorized as survived (1) or did not survive (0).;
The question is seeking the predominant outcome (survival or non-survival) among those passengers.；
The average age of passengers with this predominant outcome can also be derived from the same data set.；

sql:
SELECT age_group, COUNT(*) AS passenger_count
FROM demographics
GROUP BY age_group;
